<section id="htmlskills">
    <h2>HTML as One of My Core Skills</h2>
    <article>
        <h3>What is HTML?</h3>
        <p>HTML stands for HyperText Markup Language. It is used to create and structure web pages.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
        <h3>Structural Elements</h3>
        <p><b>&lt;header&gt;</b> – Defines the top section of a page.</p>
        <p><b>&lt;section&gt;</b> – Groups related content.</p>
        <p><b>&lt;footer&gt;</b> – Defines the bottom of a page.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
        <h3>Text Formatting Elements</h3>
        <p><b>&lt;b&gt;</b> – Makes text bold.</p>
        <p><i>&lt;i&gt;</i> – Italic text.</p>
        <p><strong>&lt;strong&gt;</strong> – Important text.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
        <h3>Lists</h3>
        <p>&lt;ul&gt; – Unordered list.</p>
        <p>&lt;ol&gt; – Ordered list.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
        <h3>Links</h3>
        <p>&lt;a&gt; – Used to create hyperlinks.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
        <h3>Images</h3>
        <p>&lt;img&gt; – Displays an image on a webpage.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
        <h3>Tables</h3>
        <p>&lt;table&gt; – Organizes data into rows and columns.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
        <h3>Forms</h3>
        <p>&lt;form&gt; – Collects user input.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
        <h3>Semantic Elements</h3>
        <p>&lt;article&gt; – Represents independent content.</p>
        <p>&lt;nav&gt; – Navigation links.</p>
    </article>
</section>

